{"type":"message","id":"60f6a305","parentId":"f8d1e4cc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:49:56.164Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pr9mbm896o3f_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5204\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1950\n[file inferred from ACTION] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\n[mutation proposed] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 014915 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight suggests compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate this hypothesis against the success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"vivid-kelp","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5204\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1950\n[file inferred from ACTION] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\n[mutation proposed] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 014915 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight suggests compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate this hypothesis against the success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774331396130}}
