{"type":"message","id":"cbeb6434","parentId":"e5118d65","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:50:02.433Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pu6w3kejf1yv_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 014915\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- There's a new key insight: \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - where Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n- The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending action items include:\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI need to create a concrete action that advances this goal. The most logical first step is to create the TIC experiment implementation. Let me check what files exist:\r\n\r\n- `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\r\n- `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\r\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` files exist\r\n\r\nThe next action should be to implement the TIC classifier. I should create a script or tool that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant or variant\r\n3. Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC experiment implementation. I'll create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the last N pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features\r\n3. Classifies invariant vs variant content\r\n4. Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending actions more carefully:\r\n- \"Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\"\r\n- \"Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\"\r\n\r\nThese are also pending. But the most important next step based on the \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" insight is the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: implement the TIC classifier script.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll investigate the existing infrastructure to determine the best integration approach for the new script.\r\n\r\nThe `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`, and `pulse_*.md` files provide a good foundation. I'll design a script that:\r\n- Parses multiple pulse log files\r\n- Extracts key semantic features\r\n- Applies a simple machine learning classification\r\n- Generates a prediction accuracy report\r\n\r\nThe implementation will leverage the existing logging and key infrastructure while introducing a novel approach to temporal invariance compression.\r\n\r\nThe script will focus on extracting and comparing invariant content across pulse logs, systematically testing prediction capabilities for subsequent pulse generation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight suggests compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate this hypothesis against the success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/tic_classifier.ps1` - a script that analyzes pulse logs to classify content as invariant (persistent across sessions) vs variant (session-specific), then tests prediction accuracy. This implements the core TIC experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogsDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier: Temporal Invariance Compression ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"PulseCount: $PulseCount, LogsDir: $LogsDir\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Get recent pulse logs sorted by date\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $PulseCount\r\n\r\nif ($pulseLogs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"[ERROR] Need at least 5 pulse logs, found $($pulseLogs.Count)\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs for analysis\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Read and parse each pulse log\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $log.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Length = $content.Length\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract invariant candidates (content appearing in multiple pulses)\r\n$invariantCandidates = @{\r\n    \"Architecture Cross-Analysis\" = 0\r\n    \"Gap-Decay Synthesis\" = 0\r\n    \"Compression-Causal Duality\" = 0\r\n    \"Breakaway is stateless\" = 0\r\n    \"Session gaps = compression\" = 0\r\n    \"Lambda parameter\" = 0\r\n    \"Phase 1\" = 0\r\n    \"Phase 2\" = 0\r\n}\r\n\r\n$variantCandidates = @{\r\n    \"Last updated\" = 0\r\n    \"Last pulse\" = 0\r\n    \"Pending\" = 0\r\n    \"Date: 2026-\" = 0\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Count occurrences\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    foreach ($key in $invariantCandidates.Keys) {\r\n        if ($pulse.Content -match $key) { $invariantCandidates[$key]++ }\r\n    }\r\n    foreach ($key in $variantCandidates.Keys) {\r\n        if ($pulse.Content -match $key) { $variantCandidates[$key]++ }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classification results\r\n$classifiedInvariant = 0\r\n$classifiedVariant = \r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:49:46"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1628,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 014915\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- There's a new key insight: \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - where Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n- The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending action items include:\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI need to create a concrete action that advances this goal. The most logical first step is to create the TIC experiment implementation. Let me check what files exist:\r\n\r\n- `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\r\n- `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\r\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` files exist\r\n\r\nThe next action should be to implement the TIC classifier. I should create a script or tool that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant or variant\r\n3. Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC experiment implementation. I'll create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the last N pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features\r\n3. Classifies invariant vs variant content\r\n4. Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending actions more carefully:\r\n- \"Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\"\r\n- \"Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\"\r\n\r\nThese are also pending. But the most important next step based on the \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" insight is the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: implement the TIC classifier script.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll investigate the existing infrastructure to determine the best integration approach for the new script.\r\n\r\nThe `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`, and `pulse_*.md` files provide a good foundation. I'll design a script that:\r\n- Parses multiple pulse log files\r\n- Extracts key semantic features\r\n- Applies a simple machine learning classification\r\n- Generates a prediction accuracy report\r\n\r\nThe implementation will leverage the existing logging and key infrastructure while introducing a novel approach to temporal invariance compression.\r\n\r\nThe script will focus on extracting and comparing invariant content across pulse logs, systematically testing prediction capabilities for subsequent pulse generation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight suggests compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate this hypothesis against the success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/tic_classifier.ps1` - a script that analyzes pulse logs to classify content as invariant (persistent across sessions) vs variant (session-specific), then tests prediction accuracy. This implements the core TIC experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogsDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier: Temporal Invariance Compression ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"PulseCount: $PulseCount, LogsDir: $LogsDir\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Get recent pulse logs sorted by date\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $PulseCount\r\n\r\nif ($pulseLogs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"[ERROR] Need at least 5 pulse logs, found $($pulseLogs.Count)\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs for analysis\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Read and parse each pulse log\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $log.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Length = $content.Length\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract invariant candidates (content appearing in multiple pulses)\r\n$invariantCandidates = @{\r\n    \"Architecture Cross-Analysis\" = 0\r\n    \"Gap-Decay Synthesis\" = 0\r\n    \"Compression-Causal Duality\" = 0\r\n    \"Breakaway is stateless\" = 0\r\n    \"Session gaps = compression\" = 0\r\n    \"Lambda parameter\" = 0\r\n    \"Phase 1\" = 0\r\n    \"Phase 2\" = 0\r\n}\r\n\r\n$variantCandidates = @{\r\n    \"Last updated\" = 0\r\n    \"Last pulse\" = 0\r\n    \"Pending\" = 0\r\n    \"Date: 2026-\" = 0\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Count occurrences\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    foreach ($key in $invariantCandidates.Keys) {\r\n        if ($pulse.Content -match $key) { $invariantCandidates[$key]++ }\r\n    }\r\n    foreach ($key in $variantCandidates.Keys) {\r\n        if ($pulse.Content -match $key) { $variantCandidates[$key]++ }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classification results\r\n$classifiedInvariant = 0\r\n$classifiedVariant = \r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:49:46","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774331402431}}
